Position Purpose
The person will be a key member of the Actimize Trade Blotter US team that is tasked to deliver multiple complex projects. This role is within the Regulatory Controls IT team. Focus will primarily be on the evolving Interactive Trade Blotter platform for Risk & Control IT, within Corporate & Institutional Banking.
The role is Java full stack developer with Python and DevOps experience in banking domain with experience of working within a dynamic and demanding environment reacting to changing business needs who works equally well as an individual or as part of a team.
Interactive Trade Blotter (ITB) is a RC IT developed reporting module running using an e database. Its purpose is to provide an electronic platform for supervisory review and sign off of trading activity by licensed Series-24 trade supervisors. There are several core features by the Trade Blotter including, but not limited to:
Workflow
System has a configurable process to route trades to trade and sales manager(s) according to the employee hierarchy
Trade Blotters
Trades from incoming Global Markets flows are distributed to supervisory trade blotters that serve as a source for exception based reporting
Exception Based reporting
Various exceptions across asset classes are used to provide supervisors with a view of daily trading activity ring on their respective desks
Global Markets Flow
System captures trading activity across all Global Market asset classes including Commodities & derivatives, Equities & derivatives, Fixed Income securities & derivatives. Activity is captured for North America Commodities, EQD and PS&F desks. Future projects will extend trade blotters to EU-APAC commodities desk, and Latin American desks.
Generic/transversal
Cross business/transaction types with customizable layouts. Ability to merge data source (e.g. client contribution, referential, market data, and other )
Access Control and Audit Trail
User g allows designating users with view only, and sign-off profiles. All user activity is captured in an audit trail, including tracking view actions (who viewed which blotters, when).
Responsibilities
Direct Responsibilities
Understand functional & system processes, do data-mapping, extract data to validate
Develop/Write Technical Design and Specifications with Trade Blotter business analysts & application users,
Create Technical Specifications document,
Coding with Agile methodology,
Develop & Execute Unit Test plan (Including writing Test Cases and Traceability Matrix).
Match user requirements to developed solutions
Conduct Workshops to train users on application usage
Automation of Deployments
L3 support
Contributing Responsibilities
Contribute towards knowledge sharing initiatives across the team
